<h1>Problem 139 - 2013 IMO, P3 of 6, G</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 9</h2>
<p>Let the excircle of triangle \(ABC\) opposite the vertex \(A\) be tangent to the side \(BC\) at the point \(A_1\). Define the points \(B_1\) on \(CA\) and \(C_1\) on \(AB\) analogously, using the excircles opposite \(B\) and \(C\), respectively. Suppose that the circumcentre of triangle \(A_1B_1C_1\) lies on the circumcircle of triangle \(ABC\). Prove that triangle \(ABC\) is right-angled.</p>
